description: When a FC ping test is finished and the instance of
hpnicfFcPingTrapOnCompletion associated with the test
is set to 'true', this notification occurred.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingCompletionNotify HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingIndex u 9999 HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingVsan u 9999 HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingAddressType i 1 HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingAddress s EXAMPLEE HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingReqPackets u 9999 HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingResPackets u 9999

description: The index of the current FC ping entry. This object
identifies a FC ping request entry uniquely in a
specified VSAN (Virtual Storage Area Network).
variables.name: HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingIndex

description: The VSAN on which the FC ping request will be
performed. If the corresponding instance value of
hpnicfFcPingOperStatus is 'inProgress', the object
cannot be modified.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingVsan

description: The type of the corresponding instance of
hpnicfFcPingAddress object.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingAddressType

description: The address to which the route will be pinged.
This object will contain an 8 octet long WWN(World Wide Name)
if the value of the associated instance of hpnicfFcPingAddressType
object is 'wwn'.
This object will contain a 3 octet long Fibre Channel Address ID
if the value of the associated instance of hpnicfFcPingAddressType
object is 'fcid'.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingAddress

description: The number of FC ping packets request in this sequence.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingReqPackets

description: The number of FC ping packets response in this sequence.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-FC-PING-MIB::hpnicfFcPingResPackets
